{"query": {"pages": {"463144": {"lastrevid": 647561498, "pageid": 463144, "canonicalurl": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interactionism", "title": "Interactionism", "editurl": "http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Interactionism&action=edit", "length": 7227, "contentmodel": "wikitext", "pagelanguage": "en", "touched": "2015-03-30T14:36:11Z", "ns": 0, "fullurl": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interactionism", "revisions": [{"*": "<div class=\"hatnote\">This article is about sociology.&#32;&#32;For the philosophy of mind, see <a href=\"/wiki/Interactionism_(philosophy_of_mind)\" title=\"Interactionism (philosophy of mind)\">interactionism (philosophy of mind)</a>.</div>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks ambox ambox-content ambox-multiple_issues compact-ambox\" role=\"presentation\"><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/40px-Ambox_important.svg.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/60px-Ambox_important.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/80px-Ambox_important.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"40\" data-file-height=\"40\" /></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><span class=\"mbox-text-span\"><table class=\"collapsible\" style=\"width:95%; background:transparent;\">\n<tr><th style=\"text-align:left; padding:0.2em 2px 0.2em 0;\"> This article has multiple issues. <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Please help <b><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Interactionism&amp;action=edit\">improve it</a></b> or discuss these issues on the <b><a href=\"/wiki/Talk:Interactionism\" title=\"Talk:Interactionism\">talk page</a></b>.</span></th></tr>\n<tr><td><table class=\"metadata plainlinks ambox ambox-content ambox-Weasel\" role=\"presentation\"><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/40px-Ambox_important.svg.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/60px-Ambox_important.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/80px-Ambox_important.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"40\" data-file-height=\"40\" /></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><span class=\"mbox-text-span\">This article <b>contains <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style/Words_to_watch#Unsupported_attributions\" title=\"Wikipedia:Manual of Style/Words to watch\">weasel words</a>: vague phrasing that often accompanies <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Neutral_point_of_view\" title=\"Wikipedia:Neutral point of view\">biased</a> or <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability\" title=\"Wikipedia:Verifiability\">unverifiable</a> information</b>.<span class=\"hide-when-compact\"> Such statements should be <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style/Words_to_watch#Improving_weasel-worded_statements\" title=\"Wikipedia:Manual of Style/Words to watch\">clarified or removed</a>.</span>  <small><i>(March 2009)</i></small><span class=\"hide-when-compact\"></span></span></td></tr></table>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks ambox ambox-style ambox-Cleanup\" role=\"presentation\"><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f2/Edit-clear.svg/40px-Edit-clear.svg.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f2/Edit-clear.svg/60px-Edit-clear.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f2/Edit-clear.svg/80px-Edit-clear.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"48\" data-file-height=\"48\" /></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><span class=\"mbox-text-span\">This article <b>may require <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Cleanup\" title=\"Wikipedia:Cleanup\">cleanup</a> to meet Wikipedia's <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style\" titl